SOURCE_NOTE:
Infant mortality rate is the number of infants dying before reaching one year of age,                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
     per 1,000 live births in a given year.
SOURCE_ORGANIZATION:
Estimates developed by the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (UNICEF, WHO,                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         
         World Bank, UN DESA Population Division) at www.childmortality.org.
